         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>On the auspicious day when the year Vikiṟama, the month of Kāṟttikai, the 24th [day],
               Friday, the thirteenth [lunar day] (tiṟiyoteci-y-um), and the constellation of Coti
               come together, the rare remedy that was obtained [broken leaf] Cuppiramaṇṇiya in
               Tiruccentu. Root-text (mūlapāṭam), examples (utāraṇam), general rules (puṟaccūttiran,
               i.e. puṟaṉaṭaiccūttiram?), summary and expansion (tokaivakai), [and] considerations
               (cintaṉai) of the Yāpparuṅkalakkārikai: in this way, all five sections are completely
               copied. The questions and answers (kaṭāviṭai) are completely copied at the end
               (kaṭaiciyiṟ).</p>
         </div>
